title: For Trade:  1917 Spandau Gew 98
postcontent: Have for trade an interesting rifle. This is a 1917 Spandau made and assembled Gew 98. Spandau only made and assembled a little over 120,000 model 98s in 1917 before switching over to machine guns. Ones after were assembled at other depot arsenal locations. This one is still in its original stock with originalreceiver and  barrel, all matching. Bore is frosted but strong rifling. It has imperial markings on stock and metal as well as a post ww1 Weimar era stamping. So it stayed in German possession. Updated in the 30s when the rear sight was changed as well as the bolt and then getting bolt and receiver blued. Vanguard is ww2 era replacement as well during upgrade.  There are various waffenampt stamping on some parts. Issued again during ww2. A survivor dating from ww1 up through the interwar years through ww2. Rifle shows wear on stock and metal. Been through alot over those years. Shoots very nice still. Looking to trade for a non sporterized sks, a Winchester 30-30 or open to a pistol or revolver. Surplus ok too.
